//Learning about JSX

const heading = React.createElement("h1" ,{id:"heading"}, "Nmaste React");
console.log(heading);

const jsxHeading = (<h1>Namaste React using JSX</h1>);
console.log(jsxHeading);

Both are same creating a element using react core and also using a heading using jsx....

the jsx code gets transpiled before going to js engine by babel 

JSX ==> React.creatElement =>ReactElement-JS Object(RENDER) => HTMLelement

